176 // Tag information for Smi.

181 template <size_t tagged_ptr_size>

184 template <int kSmiShiftSize>
185 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
186  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
187  intptr_t tagged_value =
188  (static_cast<intptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
189  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
190 }
191 
192 // Smi constants for systems where tagged pointer is a 32-bit value.
193 template <>
194 struct SmiTagging<4> {
195  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
196  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
197  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
198  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
199  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
200  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
201  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
202  }
203  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
204  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
205  }
206  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
207  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
208  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
209  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
210  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
211  //
212  // CAUTION: The original code below:
213  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
214  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
215  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
216  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
217  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
218  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) + 0x40000000U < 0x80000000U;
219  }
220 };
221 
222 // Smi constants for systems where tagged pointer is a 64-bit value.
223 template <>
224 struct SmiTagging<8> {
225  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
226  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
227  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
228  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
229  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
230  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
231  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
232  }
233  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
234  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
235  }
236  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
237  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
238  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
239  }
240 };

517 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
518 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
519 
520 template <typename T>
521 class WeakCallbackInfo {
522  public:
523  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
524 
525  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
526  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
527  Callback* callback)
528  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
529  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
530  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
531  }
532  }
533 
534  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
535  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
536  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
537 
538  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
539  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
540  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
541  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
542  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
543  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
544  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
545 
546  private:
547  Isolate* isolate_;
548  T* parameter_;
549  Callback* callback_;
550  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
551 };
552 
553 
554 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
555 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
556 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
557 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
558 // possible to request a second pass callback.
559 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

797  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
798  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
799  }
805  template <class S, class M2>
806  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
807  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
808  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
809  }
816  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
817  Copy(that);
818  }
819  template <class S, class M2>
820  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
821  Copy(that);
822  }
823  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
824  Copy(that);
825  return *this;
826  }
827  template <class S, class M2>
828  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
829  Copy(that);
830  return *this;
831  }
837  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
838  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
839  }

841  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove

848 #endif

850  }

852  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove

914  template <class S>
915  V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
916  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
917  if (this != &rhs) {
918  this->Reset();
919  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
920  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
921  }
922  return *this;
923  }
927  Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
928 
929  /*
930  * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
931  */
932  typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
933 
934  Global(const Global&) = delete;
935  void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
936 
937  private:
938  template <class F>
939  friend class ReturnValue;
940  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
941 };

6925 struct JitCodeEvent {
6926  enum EventType {
6927  CODE_ADDED,
6928  CODE_MOVED,
6929  CODE_REMOVED,
6930  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6931  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6932  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6933  };
6934  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6935  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6936  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6937  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6938  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6939  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6940 
6941  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
6942  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
6943  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
6944  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
6945  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
6946  // function.
6947  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
6948 
6949  // Type of event.
6950  EventType type;
6951  CodeType code_type;
6952  // Start of the instructions.
6953  void* code_start;
6954  // Size of the instructions.
6955  size_t code_len;
6956  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6957  Local<UnboundScript> script;
6958  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6959  // code line information which is returned from the
6960  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6961  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6962  void* user_data;
6963 
6964  struct name_t {
6965  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6966  // zero-terminated.
6967  const char* str;
6968  // Number of chars in str.
6969  size_t len;
6970  };
6971 
6972  struct line_info_t {
6973  // PC offset
6974  size_t offset;
6975  // Code position
6976  size_t pos;
6977  // The position type.
6978  PositionType position_type;
6979  };
6980 
6981  union {
6982  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6983  struct name_t name;
6984 
6985  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6986  struct line_info_t line_info;
6987 
6988  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6989  void* new_code_start;
6990  };
6991 
6992  Isolate* isolate;
6993 };

7000 enum RAILMode {
7001  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7002  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7003  // Throughput may be throttled.
7004  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7005  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7006  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7007  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7008  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7009  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7010  // in this mode.
7011  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7012  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7013  // turn off latency optimizations.
7014  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7015 };

8754 template <class T>
8755 class Maybe {
8756  public:
8757  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8758  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8759 
8763  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8764 
8769  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8770  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8771  return IsJust();
8772  }
8773 
8778  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8779  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8780  return value_;
8781  }
8782 
8787  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8788  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8789  }
8790 
8791  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8792  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8793  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8794  }
8795 
8796  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8797  return !operator==(other);
8798  }
8799 
8800  private:
8801  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8802  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8803 
8804  bool has_value_;
8805  T value_;
8806 
8807  template <class U>
8808  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8809  template <class U>
8810  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8811 };

9578  int value_offset =
9579  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9580  return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);

10112 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
10113 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10114  typedef internal::Object O;
10115  typedef internal::Internals I;
10116  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
10117  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10118  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10119  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10120  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10121  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10122  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
10123  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
10124  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
10125  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10126  reinterpret_cast<internal::NeverReadOnlySpaceObject*>(obj), value);
10127  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10128  }
10129 #endif
10130  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
10131 }

10135 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS

10138  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
10139  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10140  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10141  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10142  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10143  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||

10729 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10730  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10731  typedef internal::Internals I;
10732  const int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10733  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10734  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10735  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10736  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10737  int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10738  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10739  I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10740  const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
10741 
10742  *external_memory = amount;
10743 
10744  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10745  *external_memory_at_last_mc - *external_memory;
10746  allocation_diff_since_last_mc = allocation_diff_since_last_mc < 0
10747  ? -allocation_diff_since_last_mc
10748  : allocation_diff_since_last_mc;
10749  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10750  CheckMemoryPressure();
10751  }
10752 
10753  if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10754  *external_memory_limit += change_in_bytes;
10755  }
10756 
10757  if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10758  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10759  }
10760  return *external_memory;
10761 }
